erricht, Zwangsverheiratungen, Staatsbürgertests und die Integration muslimischer Minderheiten.Der Band versteht sich als Beitrag zur aktuellen deutschen Integrationsdebatte.  aIf in the 1980s the multicultural society was considered largely an emancipatory project, then today it provokes fears of authoritarian milieu structures which are primarily associated with Islam. Heiner Bielefeldt develops a concept of enlightened multiculturalism, the foundations and the limits of which are located in human rights. According to this concept, he analyzes the current controversies around the hijab, religious education, forced marriages, citizenship tests and the integration of Islamic minorities.This book is conceived of as a contribution to the contemporary debate in Germany around integration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aDroits de l'homme (Droit international)xAllemagne. 0aEinwanderungxGrundrechte. 0aGrundrechtexEinwanderung. 0aGrundrechtexMultikulturelle Gesellschaft. 0aHuman rightszGermany. 0aImmigrantsxGovernment policyzGermany. 0aImmigrantsxGovernment policy. 0aImmigrantsxPolitique gouvernementalexAllemagne. 0aIntégration socialexAllemagne. 0aMulticulturalismzGermany. 0aMulticulturalismexAllemagne. 0aMultikulturelle GesellschaftxGrundrechte. 0aMuslimszGermany. 0aMusulmansxAllemagne. 0aSocial integrationzGermany. 4aEinwanderung. 4aIntegration. 4aKultur. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aMensch. 4aMigration. 4aMultikulturalismus. 4aSoziologie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aHuman.  aMigration.  aSociology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Complete Package 2000-2009z9783110463415oZDB-23-TSO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highli